    "summary": "Restaurant company Darden (NYSE:DRI) met Wall Street’s revenue expectations in Q2 CY2026, with sales up 13.7% year on year to $3.72 billion. The company’s outlook for the full year was close to analysts’ estimates with revenue guided to $13.68 billion at the midpoint. Its GAAP profit of $3.51 per share was 3.6% below analysts’ consensus estimates.",
